subject: p15131736
Findings: Re-demonstrated is enlargement of the cardiomediastinal silhouette. There is elevation of the right hemidiaphragm. Evaluation of the left lung base is less than optimal due to underpenetration from overlying body habitus although no definite focal consolidation is seen. Pulmonary edema persists. No large pleural effusion seen.
Impression: Pulmonary edema and enlargement of the cardiac silhouette. No definite focal consolidation to suggest pneumonia.
